title: $:/plugins/rimir/worga/settings
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! worga settings

Two config tiddlers customise the shipped verbs and views without forking the plugin.

! `$:/config/rimir/worga/topics-stakeholder-field`

Field name read by ''Topics for context'' when deciding which topics involve a pinned person. Default `stakeholders`. Change to match your data model (e.g. `attendees`, `participants`, `team-member-of`).

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/worga/topics-stakeholder-field" tag="input" default="stakeholders"/>

! `$:/config/rimir/worga/topics-roots-filter`

Override the base "topics" filter used by ''Topics for context''. Default `[all[tiddlers]has[stakeholders]]`. Change to match how your topics are tagged / typed (e.g. `[all[tiddlers]has[kind.type]get[kind.type]match[topic]]`).

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/worga/topics-roots-filter" tag="input" default="[all[tiddlers]has[stakeholders]]"/>

! `$:/config/rimir/worga/attendees-roots-filter`

Source filter for the ''Pick attendees'' view (drilled into by the ''Start meeting'' leader). Default unions kind-typed persons and tag-typed persons so a non-kind user still has results.

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/rimir/worga/attendees-roots-filter" tag="input" default="[all[tiddlers]has[kind.type]get[kind.type]match[person]] [all[tiddlers]tag[Person]]"/>
